The photon energy is  

\[
E_{\text{photon}}=\frac{hc}{\lambda}
               =\frac{(6.626\times10^{-34}\,\text{J·s})(3.00\times10^{8}\,\text{m s}^{-1})}{100\times10^{-9}\,\text{m}}
               =1.99\times10^{-18}\,\text{J}
               =\frac{1.99\times10^{-18}}{1.602\times10^{-19}}\;\text{eV}
               \approx 12.4\;\text{eV}.
\]

The kinetic energy imparted to the electron is  

\[
K = E_{\text{photon}}-I = 12.4\;\text{eV} - 12.0\;\text{eV}=0.40\;\text{eV}
    =0.40(1.602\times10^{-19})\;\text{J}=6.4\times10^{-20}\;\text{J}.
\]

Using \(K=\frac12mv^{2}\),

\[
v=\sqrt{\frac{2K}{m_{e}}}
  =\sqrt{\frac{2(6.4\times10^{-20}\,\text{J})}{9.11\times10^{-31}\,\text{kg}}}
  \approx 3.7\times10^{5}\;\text{m s}^{-1}.
\]

\[
\boxed{3.74\times10^{5}}\,\text{ms}^{-1}
