The moment of inertia about the bisector axis (the \(y\)‑axis) is obtained from the two terminal oxygen atoms.  
With the O–O bond length \(r = 128~\text{pm}=1.28\times10^{-10}\,\text{m}\) and the O–O–O angle \(\theta =117^{\circ}\),

\[
x = r\sin\frac{\theta}{2}=1.28\times10^{-10}\,\text{m}\;
      \sin 58.5^{\circ}=1.091\times10^{-10}\,\text{m}
\]

\[
I = 2m_{\mathrm O}x^{2},
\qquad 
m_{\mathrm O}=15.994915~\text{u}=15.994915\times1.6605390666\times10^{-27}
      \,\text{kg}=2.6559\times10^{-26}\,\text{kg}
\]

\[
I = 2(2.6559\times10^{-26})(1.091\times10^{-10})^{2}
   = 6.33\times10^{-46}\,\text{kg·m}^{2}
\]

The rotational constant (in cm\(^{-1}\)) is

\[
B=\frac{h}{8\pi^{2}cI},
\qquad
h=6.62607015\times10^{-34}\,\text{J·s},
\;c=2.99792458\times10^{10}\,\text{cm·s}^{-1}
\]

\[
B=\frac{6.62607015\times10^{-34}}
        {8\pi^{2}(2.99792458\times10^{10})(6.33\times10^{-46})}
   =0.443\;\text{cm}^{-1}
\]

